pull.title: add jonasschnellis dns seeder
pull.body:
@cdecker added the server to http://bitcoinstats.com/network/dns-servers/ for monitory the quality.
Server is non-VPS root server with enough resources located in germany.

events.body: Ack, both latency and response quality are excellent.

Needs to be changed to not pass the obfuscation flag:

```
chainparams.cpp:160:104: error: no matching function for call to ‘CDNSSeedData::CDNSSeedData(const char [25], const char [30], bool)’
chainparams.cpp:160:104: note: candidates are:
chainparams.h:19:5: note: CDNSSeedData::CDNSSeedData(const string&, const string&)
chainparams.h:19:5: note: candidate expects 2 arguments, 3 provided
chainparams.h:17:8: note: CDNSSeedData::CDNSSeedData(const CDNSSeedData&)
chainparams.h:17:8: note: candidate expects 1 argument, 3 provided
```

I have no problem with this as long as @jonasschnelli agrees to (the requirements and the theory of) https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/doc/dnsseed-policy.md.
utACK if he confirms.
@TheBlueMatt i've read the dnsseed policy document some days ago and i totally agree with it.
